The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Oct. 18: The government will recruit 50,000 people in teacher posts, as non-teaching employees and in various departments by April, finance minister Asim Dasgupta said today. At a rally before the May polls, when the model code of conduct was in force, Jyoti Basu had announced the recruitment drive.

 Siliguri: Over 5,000 expired kits had been used to detect Hepatitis B and C by the medical college here and the 13 blood banks in the six North Bengal districts. A Calcutta police team was here on Wednesday to take away the kits that had not been used.

 Calcutta: The Congress lent only token support to the Trinamul demonstration against land acquisition in Singur, sending two less known leaders to its rally in Calcutta on Wednesday. 

 Calcutta: The government will soon announce its policy statement on Tata Motors Singur project, the chief min-ister has said. 




